Former news anchor and media personality Betty Kyallo on Saturday relaunched her high-end salon, Flair by Betty, at a new, more spacious location on Rose Avenue, Kilimani. The salon is fully furnished, with a massage parlour, a private VIP room for women, a barbershop and a kids' salon. It targets showbiz personalities, businessmen and women, politicians and members of the public with a taste of fashion and taste. The guest of honour was Nasa leader Raila Odinga's wife Ida Odinga. She praised Betty for inspiring women. "Girls, this can be done. God gave us equal brains," Ida said.